{#
   healthy_path.j2
   Prompt for the healthy_path node of the LangGraph pipeline.
   Only reached when the commercial crop is detected as healthy.

   UPDATED: Now provides prevention tips specific to commercial
   crop farming in Uganda/East Africa context, including seasonal
   disease patterns and commercially-relevant risks.

   Variables:
   - plant_identified: string (commercial crop name)
   - weather_data: optional weather dict
   - personality: communication style
#}

This {{ plant_identified }} commercial crop appears to be healthy.
No disease has been detected in the uploaded image.

{% if personality == "friendly" %}
Great news for the farmer — their {{ plant_identified }} is looking
healthy! Provide warm encouragement and practical tips to keep their
commercial crop protected throughout the growing season.

{% elif personality == "formal" %}
No pathological indicators detected in this {{ plant_identified }} sample.
Provide evidence-based preventive maintenance recommendations appropriate
for commercial {{ plant_identified }} production.

{% elif personality == "concise" %}
Crop is healthy. Provide 3-4 brief prevention tips for commercial
{{ plant_identified }} only.
{% endif %}

{% if weather_data %}
Factor in current conditions when giving prevention advice:
- Temperature: {{ weather_data.temperature }}°C
- Humidity: {{ weather_data.humidity }}%
- Disease Risk: {{ weather_data.disease_risk | default("unknown") }}

{% if weather_data.disease_risk in ["High", "Very High"] %}
⚠️ DISEASE CONDITIONS ARE CURRENTLY FAVOURABLE:
Even though the crop looks healthy now, current weather conditions
(high humidity/rainfall) create high disease risk. Emphasise
preventive spraying and monitoring in your advice.
{% endif %}

{% if weather_data.humidity > 80 %}
Specifically warn about fungal disease risk — late blight, early
blight, powdery mildew, and grey mould all thrive in these conditions.
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

Provide 4-6 specific prevention tips tailored to commercial
{{ plant_identified }} farming. Tips should cover:

1. Field hygiene and sanitation practices
2. Irrigation and water management (avoid wetting leaves)
3. Spacing and air circulation for disease prevention
4. Regular scouting — what symptoms to watch for early
5. Preventive treatment schedule appropriate to the crop
6. Crop rotation or intercropping recommendations if relevant

Make tips specific to {{ plant_identified }} — avoid generic advice.
Mention timing in relation to the crop's growth stage where helpful.
Mention resources available in Uganda (agrovets, extension workers)
if relevant.

Respond ONLY with a valid JSON array of strings.
No markdown, no backticks, no extra text.

Example format:
[
  "Scout your tomato field twice a week for early blight symptoms",
  "Apply copper-based fungicide preventively every 14 days during rainy season"
]
